description: Amid ongoing international instability, the event featured a speech delivered by Emmanuel Macron to the military. Photographer Julien Muguet, a regular contributor to Le Monde, documented the military ceremony.

headline: Sudden cardiac arrests in athletes reveal hidden micro-abnormalities in the heart
description: In 14 out of 19 patients who survived a ventricular fibrillation episode during physical activity, a highly detailed, in vivo electrical mapping of the heart revealed the presence of diffuse microscopic abnormalities. This occurred even though all standard tests appeared normal, according to a French study.

headline: In Angers, you can find world-class fries
description: Winning the world championship for 'authentic fries' allowed Alexandre and William Laigo, two Angers natives aged 30 and 28, to open a new, larger restaurant. Their success has been so remarkable that the two brothers now dream of launching their own franchise.

headline: Chinese police crack down on young women writing homoerotic fiction
description: Police in China have arrested young women writers over novels featuring homosexual relationships between androgynous young men. While Chinese law bans erotic content, the authorities are particularly concerned about what they see as a challenge to traditional family values.

headline: Harouna Sow, chef: 'Where I come from, men don't cook. It was a revelation for me'
description: Chef Harouna Sow, from the NGO Refugee Food, was born in Mauritania and grew up in Senegal and Mali before he came to France. He shares the story of Senegalese couscous, which reminds him of his roots and the first person who ever fed him.
